 
<p>

Future technology may enable us to burn non-fossil gases, such as
green hydrogen and methane from bio-wastes.  But we <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2022/jul/14/what-is-renewable-gas-and-is-it-really-just-around-the-corner">can't use them
in quantity in this decade</a>, and probably not in the next.

 